The other department of mythology is that with which this poem chiefly deals. lt consists of the miracles and adventures ascribed to these superhuman persons, - a vast field, in which ancient fancy rioted as freely as the modern fancy in novels and fairy-tales. Some of them may possibly be explained as a picturesqt'te way of recounting natural phenomena, or as exaggerated tales of real events.
